episodes.title: Lard of the Dance
episodes.plot: Homer and Bart try to start their own grease business; Lisa organizes a school dance.

episodes.title: The Wizard of Evergreen Terrace
episodes.plot: Homer's midlife crisis leads to a disastrous attempt at being an inventor.

episodes.title: Bart the Mother
episodes.plot: When Bart accidentally kills a mother bird, he tries to make amends by raising the eggs.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror IX
episodes.plot: Homer receives an evil hair transplant; Bart and Lisa get trapped in an Itchy and Scratchy cartoon; Maggie is revealed to be an alien.

episodes.title: When You Dish Upon a Star
episodes.plot: Homer becomes a Hollywood insider when he befriends Alec Baldwin and Kim Basinger.

episodes.title: D'oh-in' in the Wind
episodes.plot: Homer becomes a hippie after a revelation about his middle name.

episodes.title: Lisa Gets an 'A'
episodes.plot: When Lisa cheats on a test, she has a moral crisis when her perfect score qualifies the school for grant money; Homer adopts a lobster as a pet.

episodes.title: Homer Simpson in: 'Kidney Trouble'
episodes.plot: Homer gets cold feet before a transplant operation which could save Grampa's life.

episodes.title: Mayored to the Mob
episodes.plot: Homer deals with corruption when he becomes Mayor Quimby's bodyguard.

episodes.title: Viva Ned Flanders
episodes.plot: When Homer takes Ned to Las Vegas in an attempt to get him to loosen up, the two end up drunkenly marrying a pair of cocktail waitresses.

episodes.title: Wild Barts Can't Be Broken
episodes.plot: The children of Springfield revolt after a curfew is enforced.

episodes.title: Sunday, Cruddy Sunday
episodes.plot: Homer and his friends head to the Super Bowl, but are forced to sneak in when they discover their tickets are counterfeit.

episodes.title: Homer to the Max
episodes.plot: Homer changes his name to "Max Power" after discovering that he shares his name with a dimwitted TV character.

episodes.title: I'm with Cupid
episodes.plot: The husbands of Springfield plot revenge after Apu outshines them on Valentine's Day.

episodes.title: Marge Simpson in: 'Screaming Yellow Honkers'
episodes.plot: Marge's new SUV gives her a potent case of road rage.

episodes.title: Make Room for Lisa
episodes.plot: Lisa feels that her relationship with her father will never be close, and she develops stress-induced stomach pains; Marge inadvertently knocks out Milhouse.

episodes.title: Maximum Homerdrive
episodes.plot: Homer takes Bart with him on a cross-country delivery on behalf of a trucker who died before completing it; Marge and Lisa experience problems with their new novelty doorbell.

episodes.title: Simpsons Bible Stories
episodes.plot: Three famous religious stories are retold Simpsons style as the family nods off at church.

episodes.title: Mom and Pop Art
episodes.plot: Homer becomes the talk of the Springfield art community when a failed barbecue pit he worked on is mistaken for an art project.

episodes.title: The Old Man and the 'C' Student
episodes.plot: Bart is punished with community service at the Retirement Castle after he ruins Springfield's chances of hosting the Olympics.

episodes.title: Monty Can't Buy Me Love
episodes.plot: When a wealthy man moves to Springfield, Mr. Burns begins to feel that he is losing his grasp on the citizens and decides to enlist the help of Homer.

episodes.title: They Saved Lisa's Brain
episodes.plot: Lisa is invited to join the Springfield chapter of MENSA and after Mayor Quimby flees, the group ends up running the city. Meanwhile, Homer poses for a series of erotic photos.

episodes.title: Thirty Minutes Over Tokyo
episodes.plot: The Simpsons must perform on a Japanese game show after Homer loses their money on a vacation.
